23/11/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The trial of 69 Turkish citizens indicted in connection with the November 2003 bombings of British institutions and two synagogues in Istanbul continued at a local court Monday (22 November). 
The court is hearing the final submissions from prosecutors and defence attorneys. 
The defendants have been charged in the deaths of over 60 people. 
Prosecutors have demanded life sentences for the five alleged leaders of the terror cell, allegedly linked to al-Qaeda. 
(NTV - 22/11/04)
